Former Msinga municipal Chief Financial
Officer Hajra Bibi Timol was arrested by Hawks on Thursday for fraud. The Hawks members from Pietermaritzburg
Serious Commercial Crime Investigation arrested Timol (44) for fraud and money
laundering which happened at Msinga Municipality. Police spokesman Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo said
in a statement, “It is alleged that Timol was a Chief Financial Officer at
Msinga Municipality between 2016 and 2018. She allegedly caused payments to the
value of more than R2.3 million to be made into a factitious bank account that
she was in control of. In 2016, the municipality conducted an audit and
fraudulent activities were discovered. Mhlongo said, “A case of fraud was
reported at Msinga police station and the case docket was allocated to the
Hawks members for a thorough investigation. She was charged for 97 counts of
fraud and money laundering. Timol briefly appeared in the
Pietermaritzburg Magistrates’ Court yesterday and he was granted R5000 bail.
The case was postponed to 30 June 2022.  